{"name": "github-search-engine", "metadata": {"name": "Github-Search-Engine", "version": "0.2.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": "https://github.com/sachahu1/Github-Search-Engine", "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://sachahu.com/docs/github-search-engine/latest/index.html", "dependencies": ["chevron", "cleo", "githubkit", "ollama", "onnxruntime-gpu", "python-dotenv"], "summary": "Search through github issues and PRs like never before.", "upload_time": 1732559643}, "documentation": ["# Github-Search-Engine\n\n![GitHub Actions Workflow Status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/sachahu1/Github-Search-Engine/run-tests.yaml?branch=main&label=Tests)\n\n![GitHub Release](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/sachahu1/Github-Search-Engine)\n![PyPI - Python Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/github_search_engine)\n![GitHub Repo stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/sachahu1/Github-Search-Engine)\n\n## Getting Started\n\nTo get started simply install the package:\n```shell\npip install git+https://github.com/sachahu1/Github-Search-Engine.git\n```\nYou can then start using the tool with the CLI:\n```shell\ngithub_search_engine\n```\n\n### Using as a CLI tool\nYou can use this package as a CLI tool, to do that, start by indexing your favourite GitHub repository:\n```shell\ngithub_search_engine index <owner> <repository_name> --db_path=./local-store --github_access_token=<Your GitHub Personal Access Token>\n```\nThen, search through any issue using:\n```shell\ngithub_search_engine search <owner> <repository_name> \"<Your query>\"--db_path=./local-store --github_access_token=<Your GitHub Personal Access Token>\n```\n\n### Launching an API server\nYou can use this package as an API. To do that, simply run:\n```shell\ngithub_search_engine api --github_access_token=<Your GitHub Personal Access Token>\n```\n\n## Building the documentation\n### Using Docker\nTo access the documentation locally, the easiest way is to use the docker image. To do so, simply run:\n```shell\ndocker build . -f Dockerfile --target documentation -t github_search_engine-docs\ndocker run -p 80:80 -it github_search_engine-docs\n```\nThen navigate to [http://localhost](http://localhost)\n\n### Manually\nAlternatively you can build the documentation yourself.\nFirst, make sure you have the dependencies installed:\n```shell\npoetry install --with=documentation\n```\nThen build the documentation:\n```shell\npoetry run sphinx-build -M html docs/source/ docs/build\n```\nThen open the documentation in your browser:\n```shell\nopen docs/build/html/index.html\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "github_search_engine._api", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "github_search_engine._api.fastapi_package", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "github_search_engine._api.api", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "github_search_engine._api.api.lifespan", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "app", "type": {"name": "FastAPI", "xref": {"fqname": "fastapi.FastAPI", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "github_search_engine._api.api.index", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "repository", "type": {"name": "Repository", "xref": {"fqname": "github_search_engine._api.api.Repository", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "github_search_engine._api.api.search", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "owner", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "repository", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "param